# Instruction
Desktop Shortcuts are created by putting `*.desktop` files under the `~/Desktop` directory. Let's see some examples:

---

# Firefox

```bash
[Desktop Entry]
Name=Canvas
Comment=Canvas Dashboard
Exec=firefox https://canvas.vu.nl/
Icon=/home/jordi/Desktop/.icons/canvas-logo-icon.png
Terminal=false
Type=Application
Categories=Web;
```

---

# VSCode
Credit: https://github.com/microsoft/vscode/blob/main/resources/linux/code.desktop

```bash
[Desktop Entry]
Name=Dashboard
Comment=Dashboard Development
Exec=/snap/bin/code --unity-launch /home/jordi/Coding/Dashboard
Icon=/home/jordi/Desktop/.icons/vscode-logo.png
Type=Application
Terminal=false
StartupNotify=false
Categories=Utility;TextEditor;Development;IDE;
Keywords=vscode;
```

where you need to create the `Exec=/snap/bin/code` line by checking the result from `which code`.